hashi -- (c) 2017 by Harald Bögeholz

Solver for Hashiwokakero puzzles written in Haskell.
This is open source software under a BSD license, see LICENSE.

Compile with

   ghc -O2 -Wall --make solve.hs

Example use:

   ./solve 7x10easy

This will solve the sample puzzle supplied in the file 7x10easy and write
the solution to the file 7x10easy.solution.eps. Use your favorite EPS
viewer to look at the solution.

The solver can also solve 3D puzzles. In this case the output is written
to a file with the extension .solution.html in X3D format embedded in
HTML for easy viewing with a modern browser.


Harald Bögeholz
bo@ct.de
